SIMPLE: environ
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Environ
<hw>En*vi"ron</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Environed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Environing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F.
<ets>environner</ets>, fr. <ets>environ</ets> about, thereabout; pref.
<ets>en-</ets> (L. <ets>in</ets>) + OF. <ets>viron</ets> circle,
circuit, fr. OF. & F. <ets>virer</ets> to turn, LL. <ets>virare</ets> to
turn up and down, topsy-turvy. Cf. <er>Veer</er>.]</ety> <def>To
surround; to encompass; to encircle; to hem in; to be round about; to
involve or envelop.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Dwelling in a pleasant glade,⟦br⟧
With mountains round about <qex>environed</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Environed</qex> he was with many foes.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Environ</qex> me with darkness whilst I write.</q>
<rj><qau>Donne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Environ</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Environ
<hw>En*vi"ron</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety> <def>About;
around.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Lord Godfrey's eye three times <qex>environ</qex> goes.</q>
<rj><qau>Fairfax.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Environment</ent>⟦br⟧
